The most recent update of Africa’s top 10 greatest clubs has been revealed – and North African heavyweights keep a steady grip at the summit. According to Footballdatabse, Tunisian giants Esperance de Tunis still reign supreme ahead of continental rivals Al Ahly and TP Mazembe. Sudense powerhouses Al-Merreikh and Al Hilal Omdurman finish the top five with proud standings at four and five respectively. South African giants Mamelodi Sundowns stand out as the South’s challengers with a position eight claim ahead of Egyptian kings Zamalek. Meanwhile, the 2020 CAF Champions League and CAF Confederation Cup campaigns are currently underway – and the results of which will change the standings come June 2020. Clubs out of East and West Africa remain well behind the pecking order… Below is the latest top 10 rank: Source: Footmob Vanguard News The post Latest CAF Club top 10 rankings, no Nigerian club in list appeared first on Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Ahly Tripoli caused an upset by holding five-time African champions Zamalek 2-2 in Cairo and finishing runners-up. USM Alger of Algeria and Al Ahly Tripoli of Libya reached the CAF Champions League quarter-finals Sunday as 2016 runners-up Zamalek of Egypt bowed out with 10 men.A 4-1 home victory over CAPS… July 10, 2017 In "News" Lagos –Â As the 2018 Confederation of African Football (CAF) Africa Footballer of The Year award gala night draws closer, only one Nigerian, Alex Iwobi of Arsenal FC in England, made the last top 10 recently released recently by the organisers. Yes! Nigerians no doubt, are definitely happy to have one… December 23, 2018 In "News" Lagos –Â After the poor performances of Rangers International and Rivers United in the 2017 CAF Champions League, as well as similar awful display by the duo of MFM and Plateau United in this yearâ€™s premier club competition in Africa, CAF came down hard on the country, particularly as the nation… December 22, 2018 In "News"